data.chText: 使标准化；使符合标准（或规格）
data.enText: to make objects or activities of the same type have the same features or qualities; to make sth standard

data.chText: 标准化合同 / 设计 / 考试

tr: cause to conform to standard or norm
example: The weights and measures were standardized

tr: evaluate by comparing with a standard

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 standardise

value.def: To standardize things means to change them so that they all have the same features.

example.ex: There is a drive both to standardise components and to reduce the number of models on offer...
example.tran: 正在为实现零部件标准化和减少推出的型号数量而努力。

example.ex: He feels standardized education does not benefit those children who are either below or above average intelligence.
example.tran: 他认为标准化教育对那些智力水平低于或超出平均水平的儿童没有好处。

example.ex: ...the standardisation of working hours in Community countries.
example.tran: 共同体各国工作时间的统一
